# Pinterest Content API Skill

Use the local Pinterest content API running at `http://127.0.0.1:8077`.

Before generating anything, check the server:

```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://127.0.0.1:8077/health" -Method Get
```

To generate Pinterest content with one low-cost test image:

```powershell
$body = @{
  topic = "REPLACE_WITH_TOPIC"
  n = 1
  with_images = $true
  image_quality = "low"
} | ConvertTo-Json

Invoke-RestMethod `
  -Uri "http://127.0.0.1:8077/bundle" `
  -Method Post `
  -ContentType "application/json" `
  -Body $body
```

Rules:

- Do not ask for the OpenAI API key. It is already stored in the API project.
- Keep tests cheap: use `n = 1` and `image_quality = "low"` unless the user asks otherwise.
- The API has a shared `$1/day` cap across all chats/folders.
- Return the generated title, description, hashtags, board, image path, and bundle folder path.
- If the API is not reachable, tell the user to start it from `Affiliate pages master`:

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts\content_api\cli.py serve
```
